Kinrentius
can be distinguished from other genera of Bahitini as follows: head narrower then pronotum, vertex strongly concave, profemur densely setose with dorsal and lateral macrosetae irregularly arranged, anteromedian setae indistinguishable, protibia dorsal margins at right angles and without carinae, male pygofer with posterodorsal process, and aedeagus with a pair of flap-like apical processes (
).


